  <title><keyword keyref="adminUtil"/> Commands</title>
  <shortdesc/>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="author" content="Michael Khmelnitsky"/>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <refbody>
    <section><codeph><keyword keyref="adminUtilCLI"/></codeph> is the <keyword keyref="prodLong"
      /> command-line interface (CLI) administration utility. To run <codeph><keyword
          keyref="adminUtilCLI"/></codeph> commands you must <codeph>ssh</codeph> into any
        <keyword keyref="prodShort"/> node.</section>
    <section>
      <title>Global Options</title>
      <dl>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><codeph>--help</codeph>, <codeph>-h</codeph></dt>
          <dd>Show the help.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><codeph>--version</codeph>, <codeph>-v</codeph></dt>
          <dd>Print the version.</dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Commands</title>
      <dl>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><codeph>api</codeph></dt>
          <dd>Set <codeph><keyword keyref="adminUtilCLI"/></codeph> to use the specified <keyword
              keyref="prodShort"/> configuration store for subsequent operations. If an
                <codeph><varname>&lt;endpoint></varname></codeph> is not specified, the current
            endpoint is displayed.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><codeph>config</codeph></dt>
          <dd>Manipulate the configuration values of <keyword keyref="prodShort"/> components.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><codeph>help</codeph></dt>
          <dd>Show a list of commands or help for one command.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><codeph>status</codeph></dt>
          <dd>Retrieve the status of a <keyword keyref="prodShort"/> cluster.</dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Command Usage Details and Examples</title>
      <dl>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><codeph>api <varname>[&lt;endpoint>]</varname></codeph></dt>
          <dd>Example:<codeblock>$ <keyword keyref="adminUtilCLI"/> api http://hcf-consul-server.hcf:8501</codeblock></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><codeph id="config_get_example">config get</codeph>
            <codeph><varname>[options]</varname>
              <varname>&lt;key-path></varname></codeph></dt>
          <dd>Look up the current and default values of a configuration.<p>Example:</p><codeblock>$ <keyword keyref="adminUtilCLI"/> config get --json nats.user</codeblock><dl>
              <dlentry>
                <dt><codeph>--json</codeph>, <codeph>-j</codeph></dt>
                <dd>Output key-value pairs in JSON format.</dd>
              </dlentry>
            </dl></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><codeph>config set</codeph>
            <codeph><varname>[options]</varname>
              <varname>&lt;key-path></varname>
              <varname>&lt;value></varname></codeph></dt>
          <dd>Set <codeph><varname>&lt;key-path></varname></codeph> to
                <codeph><varname>&lt;value></varname></codeph> in the configuration
              store.<p>Examples:</p><codeblock>$ <keyword keyref="adminUtilCLI"/> config set -f key.name myValue.txt</codeblock><codeblock>$ echo "myValue" | <keyword keyref="adminUtilCLI"/> config set -f key.name -</codeblock><dl>
              <dlentry>
                <dt><codeph>--role</codeph>, <codeph>-r</codeph></dt>
                <dd>Set a specific <xref href="hcf-reference-roles.dita#cf_reference_roles"
                    >&lt;role></xref>'s configuration.</dd>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry>
                <dt><codeph>--file</codeph>, <codeph>-f</codeph></dt>
                <dd>Read the <codeph><varname>&lt;value></varname></codeph>.
                      <codeph><varname>&lt;value></varname></codeph> becomes either a filename to
                  read the value from or a dash (<codeph>-</codeph>) for
                  <codeph>stdin</codeph>.</dd>
              </dlentry>
            </dl></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><codeph>status <varname>[options]</varname></codeph></dt>
          <dd>
            <dl>
              <dlentry>
                <dt><codeph>--all</codeph></dt>
                <dd>Show the status of every individual
                  process.<p>Example:</p><codeblock>$ <keyword keyref="adminUtilCLI"/> status --all</codeblock></dd>
              </dlentry>
            </dl>
          </dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl>
      <draft-comment author="michaelk">
        <dl>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><codeph id="role_example">role</codeph></dt>
            <dd>Manage role containers. By default, uses the <codeph>$DOCKER_HOST</codeph>
              environment variable to determine the Docker server endpoint. Use the
                <codeph>--node</codeph> flag to start, stop, or restart a <xref
                href="hcf-reference-roles.dita#cf_reference_roles"
                ><varname>&lt;role></varname></xref> on a specific node. For example: </dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="role_start">
            <dt><codeph>role start <varname>[options]</varname></codeph></dt>
            <dd>Start the <xref href="hcf-reference-roles.dita#cf_reference_roles"
                  ><varname>&lt;role></varname></xref>.<codeblock>$ <keyword keyref="adminUtilCLI"/> role start consul</codeblock><dl>
                <dlentry>
                  <dt><codeph>--node</codeph>, <codeph>-n</codeph></dt>
                  <dd>Set the Docker server endpoint. Schemes and port number are required.
                    Supported schemes: <codeph>tcp://</codeph>
                    <codeph>unix://</codeph>
                    <codeph>http://</codeph>
                    <codeph>https://</codeph></dd>
                </dlentry>
              </dl></dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry id="role_stop_restart">
            <dt><codeph>role stop|restart <varname>[options]</varname></codeph></dt>
            <dd>Stop or restart the <xref href="hcf-reference-roles.dita#cf_reference_roles"
                  ><varname>&lt;role></varname></xref>.<codeblock>$ <keyword keyref="adminUtilCLI"/> role stop stats</codeblock><codeblock>$ <keyword keyref="adminUtilCLI"/> role restart uaa</codeblock><dl>
                <dlentry>
                  <dt><codeph>--node</codeph>, <codeph>-n</codeph></dt>
                  <dd>Set the Docker server endpoint. Schemes and port number are required.
                    Supported schemes: <codeph>tcp://</codeph>
                    <codeph>unix://</codeph>
                    <codeph>http://</codeph>
                    <codeph>https://</codeph></dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry>
                  <dt><codeph>--timeout</codeph>, <codeph>-t "0"</codeph></dt>
                  <dd>Set the number of seconds to wait before killing the container.</dd>
                </dlentry>
              </dl></dd>
          </dlentry>
        </dl>
      </draft-comment>
    </section>
